    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.44.7-8_0001" />
                <fw type="curatorial">7</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7âˆ™SKYRIM FARM</hi>
                    <lb/>
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>  
                </fw>
                <opener>
                <dateline>Oct. 14, '64</dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Slade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>What is the latest news?</p>
                
                <p>Are you enjoying the display of Autumn colors? (Ours is just barely beginning). And <hi rend="underline">have</hi> you seen Bower Aly? When he passed through Columbia, he was so busy that he did not get out to Skyrim with Mrs. Aly. I'm sure he will <del><unclear>make</unclear></del> make a fine impression If and when you see him, please tell him I sent an affectionate hello.</p>
               
                <p>I had a pleasant time in Nebraska a week ago. I read poetry at Dana College near Omaha. The crowd was from
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.44.7-8z-0002"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                    
                    many miles around, and it packed the gymnasium They gave me a "standing ovation" &#8212; an extended one! Next day the World-Herald feature-writer<sic>feature writer</sic> drove me <del><unclear>over</unclear></del> to Bancroft, Nebraska, where I did much of my best work. I left there 43 years ago, but I got a hearty reception. <del>The</del> A member of the State Centennial Commission was there too, and he says they will acquire the little cottage in which I worked and restore it. The highway marker will be erected soon with quite a ceremony, I was told. It gave me a great, happy thrill to be back there!!</p> 
               
                <p>I hope you and Nita are in fine health.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately</salute>
                <signed>John N.</signed>
                </closer>              
            </div1>
        </body>
        
